      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:141:2",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) لَا هِجْرَةَ فَوْقَ ثَلَاثٍ "
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father and Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Al Fazl Bin Shazaan, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Al Hakam, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘There should be no desertion (ceasing of relationship) for more than three (days)’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father and Muhammad ibn Isma’il from Fadl ibn Shadhan from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hisham ibn al-Hakam from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “The Messenger of Allah has said, ‘(Due to) walking out on another person (separation) should not continue more than three days.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
